        "_account_id": 292,
        "name": "James Nunez",
        "email": "jnunez@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jnunez"
      },
      "date": "2013-08-05 16:58:59.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nFirst pass of sanity tests didn't see the full OST problem. In fact, the OST throughout the tests are never very imbalanced. \n\nPatch set 1 run on Toro with ~9.77 GB OSTs.\n\nTwo instances of a single OST filling were on Toro also; \nhttps://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/951e6f9c-f985-11e2-8917-52540035b04c\nhttps://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/496f53b4-f8da-11e2-977b-52540035b04c\n\nProblem: sanity test 17m when run two times in a row fails with an error. I've seen this locally and now see it here. Need to see if this is a known problem:\nDoesn't look like LU-3129 because this wasn't an upgraded file system. So I opened LU-3696.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
