        "subject": "LU-3640 test: SANITY test 116a fails when an OST is full",
        "message": "LU-3640 test: SANITY test 116a fails when an OST is full\n\nAlthough a patch was submitted to see if an OST is full and,\nif so, the test is now skipped, this doesn't fix the problem of\nsome test filling a single OST.\n\nSo this fortestonly patch is printing the space available\non each OST after various tests in order to find out\nif the problem is a test leaving test files behind.\n\nFilling min OST 50% to see if we can get the time of this\ntest down.\n\nAlso using this to see if there is an issue with\nsetstripe in test 27A.\n\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly testlist=sanity,sanity\nSigned-off-by: James Nunez <james.a.nunez@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I46a981ad17b140c0eb4869268cb440392b2b9de4\n"
